To create a virtual machine (VM) on Google Cloud Platform using Node.js, you can use the Google Cloud Compute Engine API. You'll need to have the `@google-cloud/compute` Node.js library installed, and you must authenticate your application with Google Cloud before you can create VMs. Here's an example of how to create a simple VM instance:

```javascript
const { Compute } = require('@google-cloud/compute');
const compute = new Compute();

async function createVM() {
  // Define the VM configuration
  const zone = 'us-central1-a'; // Change to your desired zone
  const vmName = 'my-vm'; // Change to your desired VM name
  const machineType = 'n1-standard-1'; // Change to your desired machine type
  const os = 'ubuntu-1804'; // Change to your desired OS image
  const startupScript = '#!/bin/bash\necho "Hello, World" > /var/www/html/index.html'; // Change to your desired startup script

  const config = {
    os,
    http: true,
    https: true,
    machineType: `zones/${zone}/machineTypes/${machineType}`,
    metadata: {
      items: [
        {
          key: 'startup-script',
          value: startupScript,
        },
      ],
    },
  };

  // Create the VM instance
  try {
    const [vm] = await compute.createVM(zone, vmName, config);
    console.log(`VM created: ${vm.id}`);
  } catch (err) {
    console.error(`Error creating VM: ${err.message}`);
  }
}

createVM();
```

Make sure to replace the placeholders with your desired values for the zone, VM name, machine type, OS image, and startup script. Also, ensure that you have the necessary Google Cloud credentials and authentication set up.

To install the `@google-cloud/compute` library, you can use npm:

```bash
npm install @google-cloud/compute
```

Remember to configure your Google Cloud credentials by setting up a service account or using the `gcloud` command-line tool if you haven't already.

This code will create a VM with the specified configuration, including the OS image and a startup script that writes "Hello, World" to an HTML file. You can adjust the configuration to fit your specific requirements.

